    "body": "> I don't see how we can implement these:\r\n> \r\n>     * Dialog incl Accept and join button remains visible in pending or confirmed state\r\n> \r\n> \r\n> How then we access the public chat after press on \"Accept and Join chat\"? If we redirect to the chat after acceptance, how then the user will access this screen again to see the pending screen?\r\n\r\nI see, I actually thought the content could be shown on the same screen; simply remaining at the top and populating messages below. If there's no way to do that, it'll need a different design\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n>     * User can join chat without accepting Starter Pack and attributing referrer by removing the chat from the chat list and adding it again manually\r\n> \r\n> \r\n> Does this mean that we also need to show this chat in the list of user chats?\r\n\r\nYes, I think similarly I expected this to be the same public chat and was simply pointing out that the user is not 'forced' to accept in order to join the chat. There is a workaround, which means removing the chat\r\n\r\nLet's sync on chat. As this might need a different approach",
